    formula: "M = P × [r(1+r)ⁿ] / [(1+r)ⁿ − 1]\n\nWhere:\nM = Monthly Payment\nP = Loan Amount (Home Price - Down Payment)\nr = Monthly Interest Rate (Annual Rate ÷ 12)\nn = Total Payments (Years × 12)\n\nTotal Interest = (M × n) − P\nTotal Cost = Down Payment + (M × n)",
